w-metallicity globular clusters and\nultra-compact dwarf galaxies tend to follow the mass-metallicity relation like\nelliptical galaxies. The objects of FK3 are more metal-rich per unit effective\nluminosity density than high-mass ellipticals.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2012 16:31:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
